SIMPLE: freeze-dried
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: freeze-dried
<hw>freeze-dried</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <def>dried by freezing and
applying a vacuum; -- used of tissue or blood or serum or other
biological substances.</def> <note>This technique is gentler than other
drying techniques and caused less damage or deterioration to sensitive
substances. It is used primarily as a method to preserve foods or
substances, and permit storage without deterioration.</note>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> lyophilized, lyophilised.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Freeze-dry</ent>⟦br⟧
